  "text": "We constructed new materials price indexes for disaggregated industries because the BLS's Producer Price Program contains only aggregate manufacturing materials price indexes. Our materials price indexes are constructed from highly detailed commodity Producer Price Indexes (PPI) aggregated to the 2-digit SIC industry level using the information on the manufacturing industrial input}output structure from the 1982 Benchmark Input}Output Tables of the United States (1982) (U.S. Department of Commerce (1991)). These disaggregated materials price indexes are available upon request. See [CITATION_1] for more details.",
